# PURPOSE OF THIS MODULE

The compiler is the **first semantic commitment layer**.

It converts:

ParsedInput (lossless ambiguity representation)
→
CDLGraph (typed semantic execution graph)

This is the FIRST point where:
- meaning is selected
- types are enforced
- operators are bound

---

# POSITION IN PIPELINE

Input →
Parser →
Type Resolution →
Compiler →
CAS →
MECP →
Executor →
DiscourseState →
Trace

---

# HARD INVARIANTS

1. Compiler is deterministic
2. Compiler is stateless (except operator registry access)
3. Compiler MUST resolve types before graph construction
4. Compiler MAY NOT execute MECP pruning (only structure building)
5. Compiler MUST NOT mutate DiscourseState
6. Compiler MUST produce at least one valid CDLGraph or raise error

